00:45:16.020 --> 00:45:18.120
for the people, and what have you.

00:45:18.120 --> 00:45:20.220 position:56%
He said, "Let me tell you young man,

00:45:20.220 --> 00:45:24.400
in our business we
work with what exists."

00:45:24.400 --> 00:45:26.360
So we're working with what exists.

00:45:26.360 --> 00:45:29.060
With the President
of Chad and all that.

00:45:29.060 --> 00:45:31.120
And our highest priority
is security, right?

00:45:31.120 --> 00:45:33.790
Where our highest priority
is anti-terrorism.

00:45:33.790 --> 00:45:38.670
And the fact that some
tribes get left out.

00:45:38.670 --> 00:45:40.810
They don't get any
money or any resources.

00:45:40.810 --> 00:45:43.970
We've got to say, well, we'll
take care of that later;

00:45:43.970 --> 00:45:45.830
we'll work on that later you see.

00:45:45.830 --> 00:45:47.130
And their priorities.

00:45:47.130 --> 00:45:49.740
But my view is, you
work with everybody.

00:45:49.740 --> 00:45:53.850
I do not believe in
boycotting people.

00:45:53.850 --> 00:45:56.300
I would have an ambassador
in Tehran.

00:45:56.300 --> 00:45:59.480
I would have ambassadors
all over the place.

00:45:59.480 --> 00:46:02.230
I was very sorry we didn't
have an embassy in Libya

00:46:02.230 --> 00:46:04.060
for so many years you see.

00:46:04.060 --> 00:46:07.080 position:56%
You've got to work with what exists.

00:46:07.080 --> 00:46:08.690
Any other comments?

00:46:08.690 --> 00:46:12.230
I've exhausted you all.

00:46:12.230 --> 00:46:13.920
Yeah? Excuse me.

00:46:13.920 --> 00:46:15.720
Oh I'm sorry, I didn't
see you there.

00:46:15.720 --> 00:46:40.040
[ Inaudible Background Question ]

00:46:40.040 --> 00:46:45.590
&gt;&gt; Yeah, the question is, as
Africa is trying to get unified,

00:46:45.590 --> 00:46:48.880
is there a strategy to work
sort of on the entire continent,

00:46:48.880 --> 00:46:52.210
rather than region-by-region
or a country-by-country?

00:46:52.210 --> 00:46:54.380
I think there is.

00:46:54.380 --> 00:46:58.370
One thing I didn't mention
on the economic side.

00:46:58.370 --> 00:47:04.300
The Africans can make so much money
if they traded with each other.

00:47:04.300 --> 00:47:06.090
You know, you have a
billion people in Africa.

00:47:06.090 --> 00:47:07.980
Tremendous market.

00:47:07.980 --> 00:47:12.930
But yet only 10% of their
trade is with each other.

00:47:12.930 --> 00:47:17.040
You know, if they built factories,
they would have tremendous markets

00:47:17.040 --> 00:47:19.980
that could defeat China or anyone
else because it's right there.

00:47:19.980 --> 00:47:21.710
Right next door to them.

00:47:21.710 --> 00:47:26.700
And they've had a problem
with internal trade in Africa.

00:47:26.700 --> 00:47:29.170
It's hard to cross the border.

00:47:29.170 --> 00:47:31.300
Because somebody's always
looking to make money

00:47:31.300 --> 00:47:33.420
from stuff crossing the border.

00:47:33.420 --> 00:47:36.270
There are a number
of African regions

00:47:36.270 --> 00:47:39.340
which theoretically
have open borders.

00:47:39.340 --> 00:47:42.460
For example, all of the
French speaking countries.

00:47:42.460 --> 00:47:46.810
The former French colonies,
they have the same currency.

00:47:46.810 --> 00:47:48.110
So it should be easy.

00:47:48.110 --> 00:47:51.220
You can sell next door and
don't have to change your money.

00:47:51.220 --> 00:47:54.550
But it's very hard -- and
they have no terrorists.

00:47:54.550 --> 00:47:56.710
But it's very hard,
apparently, to cross the border.

00:47:56.710 --> 00:47:59.930
There's always somebody at
the border trying to do things

00:47:59.930 --> 00:48:03.630
to make it harder for you to
sell in the neighboring country.

00:48:03.630 --> 00:48:08.830
So we're encouraging the Africans
to have regional integration.

00:48:08.830 --> 00:48:13.560
Open the borders, just -- and
then, if you have a market --

00:48:13.560 --> 00:48:16.280
a potential market
of 50 million people,

00:48:16.280 --> 00:48:18.500
it's worthwhile to build a factory.

00:48:18.500 --> 00:48:22.760
But if it's only 10 million
people in a small country,

00:48:22.760 --> 00:48:24.060
it's not worth it you see.

00:48:24.060 --> 00:48:26.310
So, you make a very good point.

00:48:26.310 --> 00:48:29.530
We need to get the Africans
to work more and more together

00:48:29.530 --> 00:48:32.480
and make money from
each other, you see.

00:48:32.480 --> 00:48:34.500
And they're not doing that now.

00:48:34.500 --> 00:48:36.300
Yes, ma'am?

00:48:36.300 --> 00:49:07.130
[ Inaudible Background Question ]

00:49:07.130 --> 00:49:09.950
Oh the question is about
Cameroon, which is --

00:49:09.950 --> 00:49:12.190
you can see that towards the west.

00:49:12.190 --> 00:49:14.490
Just bordering with Nigeria.

00:49:14.490 --> 00:49:16.830
It's in blue on this map.

00:49:16.830 --> 00:49:20.900
It's fairly -- what we call the
"armpit" [laughs] of Africa.

00:49:20.900 --> 00:49:26.690
And it's always been a
very enterprising country.

00:49:26.690 --> 00:49:28.850
They do a lot of agricultural
exports.

00:49:28.850 --> 00:49:31.240
Cocoa. Coffee.

00:49:31.240 --> 00:49:34.340
And they have oil -- they have oil.

00:49:34.340 --> 00:49:38.440
And they have some ethnic
groups there like the Bamileke,

00:49:38.440 --> 00:49:40.020
who are very enterprising.

00:49:40.020 --> 00:49:43.540
They set up banks in
neighboring countries.

00:49:43.540 --> 00:49:46.330
They do transportation.

00:49:46.330 --> 00:49:48.660
So it's a very good country.

00:49:48.660 --> 00:49:54.910
Now their big problem in
Cameroon is minority rule.

00:49:54.910 --> 00:49:59.360
In fact, it's a problem that
covers a lot of countries.

00:49:59.360 --> 00:50:02.850
Let's say the army is
controlled mainly by --

00:50:02.850 --> 00:50:06.680 position:56%
not controlled, but attracts certain
people from certain ethnic groups

00:50:06.680 --> 00:50:09.330 position:56%
because they like being in the army.

00:50:09.330 --> 00:50:13.870
Cameroon, there's an ethnic
group that controls power,

00:50:13.870 --> 00:50:18.070
and it's controlled power for many
years that really represents only

00:50:18.070 --> 00:50:21.220
about 12% of the population.

00:50:21.220 --> 00:50:25.610
So a lot of people feel that
government is not for them.

00:50:25.610 --> 00:50:28.750
That they're monopolizing
resources you see.

00:50:28.750 --> 00:50:32.070
And so this -- it's kind
of a sour mood there.

00:50:32.070 --> 00:50:35.700
Except for some of the enterprising
tribes, like the Bamileke

00:50:35.700 --> 00:50:37.310
who don't give a damn
who's in power.

00:50:37.310 --> 00:50:39.520
They're out there making
money you see.

00:50:39.520 --> 00:50:44.580
But it's ethnically divided among
-- between Muslims and Christians.

00:50:44.580 --> 00:50:46.740
They get along very well.

00:50:46.740 --> 00:50:50.070
So it could be a great country.

00:50:50.070 --> 00:50:51.370
It could be a great country.

00:50:51.370 --> 00:50:54.320
But this minority rule, and
monopolizing of resources

00:50:54.320 --> 00:50:57.580
by a small group, this
is holding them back.

00:50:57.580 --> 00:51:00.630
Really holding them back.

